The paper deals with deep implicit generative modeling, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper proposes a new approach to learning an Implicit Generative Model (IGM) using a characteristic function distance (CFD) measure. This approach has applications in unsupervised image generation, which suggests that the paper could be categorized under computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper proposes a variation of the CFD that optimizes the weighting distribution parameters during training, which involves optimization techniques that are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the computational complexity of the proposed method, which could be of interest to researchers in information theory (cs.IT) who are concerned with efficient algorithms. Overall, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.IT.
